org.jlinalg.f2
Class F2

java.lang.Object
  org.jlinalg.RingElement<RE>
      org.jlinalg.FieldElement<F2>
          org.jlinalg.f2.F2
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<F2>, IRingElement<F2>
public class F2
extends FieldElement<F2>

This class represents an element of the modulo 2 field F2. F2 is a field, just like the rational numbers are. At first glance it seems to be a rather academic example, but prime fields (especially F2) have numerous applications (e.g.: error correcting codes).

Author:
Andreas Keilhauer, Georg Thimm
